<p>Peru’s capital saw youth-led demonstrations demanding the resignation of new president José Jerí, with clashes in Lima leaving one person dead and about 100 people injured [apnews.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. The government said it will declare a state of emergency in Lima, and the prime minister indicated it would take effect within hours amid anger over rising crime [theguardian.com#1][dw.com#1][france24.com#1]. Jerí rejected calls to step down, framing his role as safeguarding national stability [scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]. The unrest comes days after Congress removed former president Dina Boluarte, with Jerí taking office on Oct. 10 [france24.com#1][mercopress.com#1]. Authorities said they are investigating the shooting that caused the fatality [scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/8-oXixXHlRVwV_DV2Ebc-TzFNx723Mcouyp2_wmn_VRO_Cmll9HnN5SLH13s6o40u7e9DF6XVf90y6D2f-PXTuicTHzcaK3YxW-8ZvQH8KyyrKnuApFnLSTWPuQmqqukdphgWgTQzahHgem6B3bC7prUYNxMjYq0rAmoFcrUwEVYHps7rzTopBcCiW5R4Nmabd-6rmtUFnlX0JDX4_ebM9Ws7QBdespY-HrhgmCwrleo86JV9DcVKpqZKmI' alt='Police and protesters face off near Peru&#x27;s Congress during demonstrations in Lima.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Injury breakdown: Authorities reported roughly 100 injuries, including about 80 police officers and 10 journalists, while the fatal shooting is under investigation [thehindu.com#1][scmp.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1].</li><li>Youth mobilization: Gen Z activists have been central to organizing the demonstrations, leveraging social media platforms such as TikTok to coordinate actions [apnews.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li><li>Impeachment pressure: Peru’s unicameral Congress initiated proceedings toward impeaching Acting President José Jerí less than a week after he took office [mercopress.com#1].</li><li>Clash hotspots: Hundreds of protesters clashed with police outside the Congress building in central Lima during the unrest [straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Security measures: The prime minister said the state of emergency in Lima would be declared within hours and that a package of measures to tackle insecurity is being prepared [theguardian.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>My responsibility is to maintain the stability of the country; that is my responsibility and my commitment - President José Jerí</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Prime Minister Ernesto Alvarez: Announced a state of emergency would be declared in Lima within hours and said the government is preparing measures to address public insecurity. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/17/peru-protests-state-emergency-president-jose-jeri'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Gen Z protest organizers: Demand that President Jerí resign following the deadly clashes during the demonstrations. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329389/perus-new-president-refuses-resign-gen-z-led-protests-turn-violent'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Peru’s Congress: Launched proceedings toward impeaching Acting President Jerí amid widespread discontent over corruption and insecurity. (<a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2025/10/17/peru-s-acting-president-on-the-brink-of-impeachment-after-less-than-a-week'>MercoPress</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/one-dead-dozens-injured-as-perus-new-president-faces-widespread-protests'>One dead, dozens injured as Peru’s new president faces widespread protests</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329389/perus-new-president-refuses-resign-gen-z-led-protests-turn-violent'>Peru’s new president refuses to resign as Gen Z-led protests turn violent</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/peru-to-impose-state-of-emergency-after-protests-turn-deadly/a-74393642'>Peru to impose state of emergency after protests turn deadly</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/p